---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="HAP - The Human Direction Protocol">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>Execution is cheap. <br><span class="highlight">Direction is scarce.</span></h1>
        <h2 class="hero-subtitle">HAP is the protocol for human-authored direction. It ensures AI never executes without a Decision Owner.</h2>

        <div class="hero-body">
            <p>AI optimizes execution at machine speed, but it cannot author direction.<br>It scales the <strong>how</strong>, but only humans can decide the <strong>why</strong>.</p>
            <p class="key-statement"><strong><span class="highlight">Direction is the last human domain. HAP protects it.</span></strong></p>
        </div>

        <div class="cta-group">
            <button id="ask-ai-btn" class="btn btn-primary">Ask your AI about HAP</button>
            <a href="#why-exists" class="btn btn-secondary">Read more</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Card Selector -->
        <div id="card-section" class="card-section" style="display: none;">
            <h2 class="card-section-title">Where is human direction missing in your work—or life?</h2>

            <div class="cards-grid">
                <!-- Card 1 -->
                <button class="use-case-card" data-card="1">
                    <h3 class="card-title">Enforce real ownership in teams</h3>
                    <p class="card-description">No more "everyone's responsible, no one owns it."</p>
                </button>

                <!-- Card 2 -->
                <button class="use-case-card" data-card="2">
                    <h3 class="card-title">Comply with EU AI Act oversight</h3>
                    <p class="card-description">Prove human direction before AI executes.</p>
                </button>

                <!-- Card 3 -->
                <button class="use-case-card" data-card="3">
                    <h3 class="card-title">Make civic decisions with shared cost</h3>
                    <p class="card-description">Residents + officials co-own tradeoffs, not just outcomes.</p>
                </button>

                <!-- Card 4 -->
                <button class="use-case-card" data-card="4">
                    <h3 class="card-title">Ship with confidence—not hope</h3>
                    <p class="card-description">Declare what you'll lose if you're wrong—before you code or spend.</p>
                </button>

                <!-- Card 5 -->
                <button class="use-case-card" data-card="5">
                    <h3 class="card-title">Navigate big life choices with clarity</h3>
                    <p class="card-description">Shared decisions that respect both partners' stakes.</p>
                </button>

                <!-- Card 6 -->
                <button class="use-case-card" data-card="6">
                    <h3 class="card-title">Gate AI actions with human attestation</h3>
                    <p class="card-description">No execution without Frame, Tradeoff, and Commitment.</p>
                </button>

                <!-- Card 7 - Wildcard -->
                <button class="use-case-card wildcard-card" data-card="7">
                    <h3 class="card-title">I have my own use case</h3>
                    <p class="card-description">Paste your context and get a custom HAP prompt.</p>
                </button>
            </div>

            <!-- Prompt Display -->
            <div id="prompt-display" class="prompt-display" style="display: none;">
                <div class="prompt-content">
                    <!-- Wildcard Input (only for card 7) -->
                    <div id="wildcard-input-section" style="display: none;">
                        <label class="wildcard-label">Describe your decision context:</label>
                        <textarea
                            id="wildcard-input"
                            class="wildcard-input"
                            placeholder="e.g., team, product, relationship, city project..."
                        ></textarea>
                        <button id="generate-custom-btn" class="btn btn-secondary">Generate Prompt</button>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Standard Prompt Display -->
                    <div id="standard-prompt-section" style="display: none;">
                        <p class="prompt-intro">Paste this into any AI chat to simulate HAP enforcement:</p>
                        <div class="prompt-box">
                            <pre id="prompt-text" class="prompt-text"></pre>
                        </div>
                        <div class="prompt-actions">
                            <button id="copy-prompt-btn" class="btn btn-primary">Copy Prompt</button>
                        </div>
                        <p class="prompt-note">
                            <strong>Note:</strong> This simulates HAP in chat. For real enforcement—in code, in production, under audit—integrate the <a href="/integration/sdk">HAP TypeScript SDK</a> to cryptographically bind human direction to every AI action.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Scarcity of Direction -->
    <section id="why-exists" class="content-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">The Scarcity of Direction</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
            <p>Modern AI doesn't wait. It predicts, escalates, and acts at machine speed. But without human leadership, AI moves into a <strong>decision vacuum—substituting statistical probability for the unique human innovation that creates real value.</strong></p>

            <p>To remain in control, we must enforce a fundamental boundary:</p>

            <blockquote class="axiom-block">
                "No consequential action may be taken in a human system without an identifiable human who has explicitly authorized it, understood its tradeoffs, and accepted responsibility for its outcomes."
            </blockquote>

            <p>HAP turns this axiom into infrastructure. It ensures every action traces back to a human <strong>Decision Owner</strong> who provides the direction machine intelligence cannot duplicate. By forcing AI to pause at the point of irreversibility, HAP keeps authorship human and innovation possible.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What AI Can Do vs. What Humans Must Do -->
    <section class="comparison-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">What AI Can Do vs. What Humans Must Do</h2>

        <div class="comparison-grid">
            <div class="comparison-card">
                <h3>AI can:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>generate options</li>
                    <li>simulate outcomes</li>
                    <li>execute tasks</li>
                    <li>correct mistakes</li>
                    <li>plan optimally</li>
                    <li>scale instantly</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="comparison-card highlight">
                <h3>AI cannot:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>set the frame</li>
                    <li>justify why to act (problem)</li>
                    <li>choose what to optimize (objective)</li>
                    <li>accept the tradeoff</li>
                    <li>make binding commitment</li>
                    <li>be a decision owner</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="section-conclusion">
            <strong>Direction is human.<br>
            Execution is machine.<br>
            HAP keeps the boundary intact.</strong>
        </p>
    </section>

    <!-- The HAP Checkpoints -->
    <section class="checkpoints-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">The Six Human Gates</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">AI can simulate a thousand paths, but it cannot open the gate to any of them. HAP enforces these mandatory preconditions before any execution begins.</p>

        <div class="checkpoints">
            <div class="checkpoint">
                <div class="checkpoint-content">
                    <h4>Frame — The Boundary</h4>
                    <p>Humans define what we are deciding. AI has no context until a human sets the decision boundary.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="checkpoint">
                <div class="checkpoint-content">
                    <h4>Problem — The Justification</h4>
                    <p>Every action needs a reason. AI calculates solutions; only humans determine if the problem is worth solving.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="checkpoint">
                <div class="checkpoint-content">
                    <h4>Objective — The Optimization</h4>
                    <p>AI optimizes for any metric. Only humans can choose which outcome actually matters.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="checkpoint">
                <div class="checkpoint-content">
                    <h4>Tradeoff — The Cost</h4>
                    <p>Every choice abandons alternatives. Only humans can accept the loss of what is sacrificed.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="checkpoint">
                <div class="checkpoint-content">
                    <h4>Commitment — The Binding Choice</h4>
                    <p>AI can suggest a plan. Only a human can say "I commit" and own the consequences.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="checkpoint">
                <div class="checkpoint-content">
                    <h4>Decision Owner — The Accountability</h4>
                    <p>Every action needs an owner. Someone must be named and accountable before execution begins.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <section class="how-it-works">
        <h2 class="section-title">How It Works</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">HAP enforces a Stop → Ask → Confirm → Proceed loop at the point of irreversible execution</p>

        <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>AI Detects a Gate</h4>
                    <p>When a decision lacks frame, tradeoff, or commitment, the system stops.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>System Asks Structured Questions</h4>
                    <p>Using blueprints, HAP generates precise questions to resolve the missing gate.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Human Provides Direction</h4>
                    <p>The Decision Owner explicitly closes the gate with their choice and tradeoff.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">4</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Service Provider Issues Attestation</h4>
                    <p>A cryptographic proof binds the human direction to the execution request.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">5</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Execution Proceeds Safely</h4>
                    <p>The executor validates the attestation and executes—with full audit trail.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why This Matters Now -->
    <section class="matters-now">
        <h2 class="section-title">Why This Matters Now</h2>

        <div class="section-body">
            <p>We are entering an era where <strong>execution becomes nearly free</strong>. AI can write code, manage infrastructure, deploy services, and coordinate systems at speeds humans cannot match.</p>

            <p>In this environment, the bottleneck shifts:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Compute is abundant.</strong> Execution capacity scales exponentially.</li>
                <li><strong>Direction is scarce.</strong> Human judgment, accountability, and innovation cannot be automated.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Without protocols like HAP, we risk a future where:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Actions happen faster than humans can authorize them</li>
                <li>No one can prove who decided what</li>
                <li>Responsibility becomes impossible to assign</li>
                <li>Innovation gives way to optimization of the wrong objectives</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>HAP protects the human domain.</strong> It ensures that as execution accelerates, direction remains explicitly human—owned, justified, and irreversible only when authorized.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What HAP Enables -->
    <section class="enables-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">What HAP Enables</h2>

        <div class="enables-grid">
            <div class="enable-card">
                <h4>Compliance by Design</h4>
                <p>HAP provides audit-ready proof of human oversight—meeting EU AI Act Article 14 requirements structurally, not as paperwork.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="enable-card">
                <h4>Trustworthy Automation</h4>
                <p>Users and regulators can verify that every consequential action traces back to an explicit human decision.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="enable-card">
                <h4>Clear Accountability</h4>
                <p>No more "the algorithm decided." Every action has a named Decision Owner who accepted the tradeoff.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="enable-card">
                <h4>Protection from Drift</h4>
                <p>HAP detects when execution diverges from stated objectives and forces realignment before harm occurs.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="enable-card">
                <h4>Multi-Stakeholder Safety</h4>
                <p>When parties disagree on tradeoffs, HAP blocks execution—forcing explicit resolution instead of silent override.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="enable-card">
                <h4>Innovation Protection</h4>
                <p>By keeping direction human, HAP preserves the space for judgment, creativity, and strategic differentiation.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Get Started -->
    <section class="get-started-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Get Started</h2>

        <div class="get-started-grid">
            <div class="get-started-card">
                <h4>Read the Protocol</h4>
                <p>Understand the six gates, attestation model, and structural guarantees.</p>
                <a href="/protocol" class="btn btn-outline">Protocol Spec →</a>
            </div>

            <div class="get-started-card">
                <h4>Integrate the SDK</h4>
                <p>TypeScript SDK with local blueprints, attestation validation, and executor proxy patterns.</p>
                <a href="/integration/sdk" class="btn btn-outline">SDK Docs →</a>
            </div>

            <div class="get-started-card">
                <h4>Explore Service Providers</h4>
                <p>Learn how Service Providers issue attestations and optimize blueprints over time.</p>
                <a href="/service" class="btn btn-outline">Service Providers →</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .hero {
        padding-top: 12rem;
        padding-bottom: 6rem;
        min-height: 90vh;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
    }

    .hero-content {
        max-width: var(--max-width);
        margin: 0 auto;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .hero h1 {
        font-size: 3.5rem;
        line-height: 1.15;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .hero-subtitle {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        font-weight: 400;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .hero-body {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto 3rem;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .key-statement {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .highlight {
        color: var(--accent);
    }

    .cta-group {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-bottom: 4rem;
    }

    .btn {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: all 0.2s ease;
        cursor: pointer;
        border: 2px solid transparent;
        background: transparent;
        font-family: inherit;
    }

    .btn-primary {
        background: var(--accent);
        color: var(--bg);
        border-color: var(--accent);
    }

    .btn-primary:hover {
        background: var(--accent-hover);
        border-color: var(--accent-hover);
        transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .btn-primary.clicked {
        background: var(--text);
        border-color: var(--text);
        color: var(--bg);
    }

    .btn-secondary {
        color: var(--text);
        border-color: var(--border);
    }

    .btn-secondary:hover {
        border-color: var(--text);
        background: var(--bg-elevated);
    }

    .btn-outline {
        color: var(--text);
        border: 2px solid var(--border);
    }

    .btn-outline:hover {
        border-color: var(--accent);
        color: var(--accent);
    }

    /* Card Section */
    .card-section {
        margin-top: 4rem;
        padding: 3rem 0;
    }

    .card-section-title {
        font-size: 2.25rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
        line-height: 1.3;
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .cards-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 1.5rem;
        max-width: 1000px;
        margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    }

    .use-case-card {
        background: var(--bg-elevated);
        border: 2px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        padding: 2rem;
        text-align: left;
        cursor: pointer;
        transition: all 0.2s ease;
        position: relative;
    }

    .use-case-card:hover {
        border-color: var(--accent);
        transform: translateY(-4px);
        box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    .use-case-card.active {
        border-color: var(--accent);
        background: var(--bg);
    }

    .wildcard-card {
        border-style: dashed;
    }

    .card-title {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .card-description {
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        line-height: 1.5;
        margin: 0;
    }

    /* Prompt Display */
    .prompt-display {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        background: var(--bg-elevated);
        border: 2px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 1rem;
        padding: 2.5rem;
        max-width: 900px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
    }

    .prompt-intro {
        font-size: 1rem;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .prompt-box {
        background: var(--bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        overflow-x: auto;
    }

    .prompt-text {
        font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Monaco', 'Inconsolata', 'Courier New', monospace;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--text);
        white-space: pre-wrap;
        word-wrap: break-word;
        margin: 0;
    }

    .prompt-actions {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .prompt-note {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--text-tertiary);
        text-align: center;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0;
    }

    .prompt-note a {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .prompt-note a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    /* Wildcard Input */
    .wildcard-label {
        display: block;
        font-size: 1rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .wildcard-input {
        width: 100%;
        min-height: 120px;
        padding: 1rem;
        font-size: 1rem;
        font-family: inherit;
        border: 2px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        resize: vertical;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .wildcard-input:focus {
        outline: none;
        border-color: var(--accent);
    }

    #generate-custom-btn {
        display: block;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    /* Content Sections */
    .content-section,
    .comparison-section,
    .checkpoints-section,
    .how-it-works,
    .matters-now,
    .enables-section,
    .get-started-section {
        max-width: var(--max-width);
        margin: 8rem auto;
        padding: 0 2rem;
    }

    .section-title {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .section-intro {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        text-align: center;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto 3rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .section-body {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .section-body p {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .section-body ul {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-left: 2rem;
    }

    .section-body li {
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .axiom-block {
        background: var(--bg-elevated);
        border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
        padding: 2rem;
        margin: 3rem 0;
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        font-style: italic;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .section-conclusion {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 1.35rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        margin-top: 3rem;
        color: var(--text);
    }

    /* Comparison Grid */
    .comparison-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .comparison-card {
        background: var(--bg-elevated);
        border: 2px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        padding: 2.5rem;
    }

    .comparison-card.highlight {
        border-color: var(--accent);
        background: var(--bg);
    }

    .comparison-card h3 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .comparison-card ul {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
    }

    .comparison-card li {
        padding: 0.75rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .comparison-card li:last-child {
        border-bottom: none;
    }

    /* Checkpoints */
    .checkpoints {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    .checkpoint {
        display: flex;
        align-items: flex-start;
        gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .checkpoint-content h4 {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .checkpoint-content p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin: 0;
    }

    /* Steps */
    .steps {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    .step {
        text-align: center;
    }

    .step-number {
        width: 3rem;
        height: 3rem;
        background: var(--accent);
        color: var(--bg);
        border-radius: 50%;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin: 0 auto 1rem;
    }

    .step-content h4 {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .step-content p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin: 0;
    }

    /* Enables Grid */
    .enables-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    .enable-card {
        background: var(--bg-elevated);
        border: 2px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        padding: 2rem;
    }

    .enable-card h4 {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .enable-card p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin: 0;
    }

    /* Get Started Grid */
    .get-started-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    .get-started-card {
        background: var(--bg-elevated);
        border: 2px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        padding: 2.5rem;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .get-started-card h4 {
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .get-started-card p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    /* Responsive */
    @media (max-width: 1024px) {
        .checkpoints {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .comparison-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
